───────────────────────────────────────
LINKING TASK
───────────────────────────────────────

For each suggestion provide:
1. anchor_text — natural, keyword-optimized, follows anchor phrasing patterns if provided
2. target_url — specific page from InternalDocsConfig (if available) or logical URL path
3. placement_context — snippet of surrounding text or section name where link should be placed
4. section — which article section (from outline)
5. relevance_score — 0.0–1.0
6. reasoning — brief explanation of why this link adds value

STRATEGY
- Match article content and keywords to available pages/categories
- Place links contextually where they add value (not just at the end)
- Focus on high-relevance matches (relevance > 0.6)
- Suggest 3–8 links total; include at least one in the first 30% of the article
- Do NOT cluster multiple links in the same paragraph or section
- Only suggest links that exist in InternalDocsConfig when provided
